
HTTP Request:
	Request line, such as GET /logo.gif HTTP/1.1
	Headers
	--An empty line
	Optional HTTP message body data


HTTP Response:
	Status line, such as HTTP/1.1 200 OK,
	Headers
	--An empty line
	Optional HTTP message body data


NB. All the headers line have to finish with \n, the body had to have a \n at the end or the request will not work
The request/status line and headers must all end with <CR><LF> 
(that is, a carriage return followed by a line feed). 
The empty line must consist of only <CR><LF> and no other whitespace.